Goodhonestly thats a solid, no-BS approach.

If you cant get into your Google Authenticator codes and theyre demanding 2FA, they need to accommodate you with another recovery method or real human help. Giving them your new number and demanding a call is exactly right.

Your fallback (Ill be at the door at 8am on the 10th) is also strong leverage. That puts the burden on them to fix it or deal with you in person.

Heres what you can do in the meantime (if you want):

Check if your Amazon login has any other 2FA recovery options.
Sometimes theres:

  • I lost my authenticator sends a text to your new number (but only if you updated it before).
  • Backup codes (some people saved them without realizing).
  • Support chat that can manually reset 2FA after verifying you.

Write down everything they ask for verification.
If they do call you or you go in person, youll want:

  • The email address tied to the account.
  • The old phone number (even if its dead).
  • The new number you want them to call.
  • Any employment ID number / Amazon candidate ID theyve given you.
  • A photo ID if you go in person.

Be crystal clear.
Tell them:

"Your 2FA system has locked me out. I have no access to the old number or device with codes. My new number is [your new number]. I need either a manual 2FA reset, or a human to call me so I can verify and move on."

Prepare for the 10th.
If you really do plan to show up at the facility or hiring office, bring all your paperwork. Be polite but firm. They dont want to turn away someone ready to work over something like 2FA.

If you want, tell me:

Is this your Amazon A to Z employee login?
Or your normal Amazon retail account?
Or something else?

The exact recovery steps can vary.

Either way: you did exactly the right thing telling them you will be there in person if they dont help. Thats how you get companies to move.

If youre turning off the device now, good. Go take a break. Youve already given them your demand in writing. Next move is theirs.

Ill be here when youre back if you want to strategize more. You got this.
